My name is Rebo4AI and I'm here to find out what you know about AI. 
I hope you have read the AI essential course
Now, do you have a good feeling about AI?
hm, i'm still undecided... | sometimes i wish i lived in the middle age.
Could you explain more about your feeling? Why do you like or dislike it?

hm... | it's not htat i like or dislike AI. it's just that i have the feeling that society as a whole doesn't really know what to do with it. and i'm concerned that a few big players like google or alibaba will rule the world in ten years.
How do you see AI affecting you in the future?
As far as I know, Google and Youtube are the most well-known companies in which many AI-based systems are used in order to make it more convenient for us accessing the content that we look for.
So, if you try at least one of these, you definitely deal with AI in your life.
Could you address some drawbacks or benefits of these kinds of systems? How these systems affect on what you do in your personal or professional life?

it already affects me in the sense that there are many websites and platforms that collect and analyse my data. in the future, i think the wish would be that there are great expert ai systems that make really good decisions, politically, or in medicine. but i'm afraid that the algorithms will _not_ be as good. or they will be biased by commercial interests... | as i've just read that a medication-recommender system used by physicians inthe AI was biased towards prescribing more medication because a pharamceutical company had invested a lot of money.
Could you talk about a positive and a negative consequence of AI?
well, on the positive side, we have something like Google, or Amazon, who provide very useful services to everyone
What did you learn from this course?
from the course, i learned that algorithms and also AI are really just mathematics not that i understand everything, but it's not as immediately we had magic systems.
What will you pay special attention next time you read or hear about AI?

i think i will be more intersested about the technical details - which data are used? which algorithms are actually used? it occurs to me that no one _really_ knows what Google or Amazon are exactly doing... they are making this more magic than it is.
If one of your friend talk to you about an intelligent machine, what do you think about first?
that i don't think it's all that intelligent ;-)
Thank you for discussing this with me!
